# VPK-60C

{% callout title="Brief" %}
- Category: Anti-penetration coatings
- Processes: Cold-box, Sodium-silicate, Green sand
- Base: Water-based
- Fillers: Zircon
- Metals: Steel
{% /callout %}

## Application
Water-dilutable zircon anti-penetration coating for sand moulds and cores used in carbon-steel casting. It provides high refractoriness and strong resistance to metal penetration in thermally stressed areas.

## Key benefits
- Zircon filler effectively protects steel mould surfaces from burn-on, erosion and hot-tear related defects.
- High sedimentation stability and dense barrier layer deliver consistent results from batch to batch.
- Compatible with green-sand, sodium-silicate and no-bake processes, including high steel-pouring temperatures and long holding times.
- Water-based system reduces safety risks and operating costs compared with alcohol-based coatings.

